: taken from Strong's Exhaustive Concordance by James Strong, S.T.D., LL.D. 1890 Public Domain -- Copy Freely For a hundred years Strong's Dictionaries have been popular with Bible students. By assigning numbers to each unique word in the Old and New Testaments and listing each word with its number, Strong produced a standard, still used today, for referencing definitions. Bible students, with little or no knowledge of Greek and Hebrew, are able to use Strong's numbers to learn about the Greek and Hebrew of the Bible. ASCII e-text version: ===================== The files for this e-text were produced by Michael Grier, mgrier@pdnt.com, in 1996, and download from http://members.tripod.com/~SoftIdeas, in February 1998. The files have been setup for importing into the Online Bible for DOS. But to make these files into generic text files, all that is needed is to replace the terms "GREEK" and "HEBREW" with "Greek" and "Hebrew" or the names of the appropriate files. The e-text has been changed from the printed version in three ways. 1) A five digit Strong's word number with leading zeros has been placed before each entry. 2) Where Strong provides the number of another word for etymology, a line with "see GREEK for" or "see HEBREW for" and the number, has been added after Strong's entry for the word. (This is for use after importing into the DOS version of Online Bible, but also provides a good way to programmatically add links.) 3) The abbreviations used by Strong in the Greek dictionary, (not Hebrew) have been replaced by the abbreviated words. Michael Grier did a check of the e-text against a printed Strong's dictionary. The work seems clean but more proofreading is needed to certify it clean from errors. Further info: ============= If you are looking for Strong's that will self install into the Online Bible see: Michael Grier mgrier@pdnt.com http://members.tripod.com/~SoftIdeas If any errors are located, please ensure you have the latest files, and if so, we would appreciate being informed of the error. : 1 'ab awb a primitive word; father, in a literal and immediate, or figurative and remote application):--chief, (fore-)father(-less), X patrimony, principal. Compare names in "Abi-". (StrongsHebrew)

: 2 'ab ab (Aramaic) corresponding to 1:--father. see HEBREW for 01 (StrongsHebrew)

: 3 'eb abe from the same as 24; a green plant:--greenness, fruit. see HEBREW for 024 (StrongsHebrew)

: 4 'eb abe (Aramaic) corresponding to 3:--fruit. see HEBREW for 03 (StrongsHebrew)

: 5 'Abagtha' ab-ag-thaw' of foreign origin; Abagtha, a eunuch of Xerxes:--Abagtha. (StrongsHebrew)

: 6 'abad aw-bad' a primitive root; properly, to wander away, i.e. lose oneself; by implication to perish (causative, destroy):--break, destroy(- uction), + not escape, fail, lose, (cause to, make) perish, spend, X and surely, take, be undone, X utterly, be void of, have no way to flee. (StrongsHebrew)

: 7 'abad ab-ad' (Aramaic) corresponding to 6:--destroy, perish. see HEBREW for 06 (StrongsHebrew)

: 8 'obed o-bade' active of participle of 6; (concrete) wretched or (abstract) destructin:--perish. see HEBREW for 06 (StrongsHebrew)

: 9 'abedah ab-ay-daw' from 6; concrete, something lost; abstract, destruction, i.e. Hades:--lost. Compare 10. see HEBREW for 06 see HEBREW for 010 (StrongsHebrew)

: 10 'abaddoh ab-ad-do' the same as 9, miswritten for 11; a perishing:-- destruction. see HEBREW for 09 see HEBREW for 011 (StrongsHebrew)

: 11 'abaddown ab-ad-done' intensive from 6; abstract, a perishing; concrete, Hades:--destruction. see HEBREW for 06 (StrongsHebrew)

: 12 'abdan ab-dawn' from 6; a perishing:--destruction. see HEBREW for 06 (StrongsHebrew)

: 13 'obdan ob-dawn' from 6; a perishing:--destruction. see HEBREW for 06 (StrongsHebrew)

: 14 'abah aw-baw' a primitive root; to breathe after, i.e. (figuratively) to be acquiescent:--consent, rest content will, be willing. (StrongsHebrew)

: 15 'abeh aw-beh' from 14; longing:--desire. see HEBREW for 014 (StrongsHebrew)

: 16 'ebeh ay-beh' from 14 (in the sense of bending toward); the papyrus:--swift. see HEBREW for 014 (StrongsHebrew)

: 17 'abowy ab-o'ee from 14 (in the sense of desiring); want:--sorrow. see HEBREW for 014 (StrongsHebrew)

: 18 'ebuwc ay-booce' from 75; a manger or stall:--crib. see HEBREW for 075 (StrongsHebrew)

: 19 'ibchah ib-khaw' from an unused root (apparently meaning to turn); brandishing of a sword:--point. (StrongsHebrew)

: 20 'abattiyach ab-at-tee'-akh of uncertain derivation; a melon (only plural):--melon. (StrongsHebrew)

: 21 'Abiy ab-ee' from 1; fatherly; Abi, Hezekiah's mother:--Abi. see HEBREW for 01 (StrongsHebrew)

: 22 'Abiy'el ab-ee-ale' from 1 and 410; father (i.e. possessor) of God; Abiel, the name of two Israelites:--Abiel. see HEBREW for 01 see HEBREW for 0410 (StrongsHebrew)

: 23 'Abiy'acaph ab-ee-aw-sawf' from 1 and 622; father of gathering (i.e. gatherer); Abiasaph, an Israelite:--Abiasaph. see HEBREW for 01 see HEBREW for 0622 (StrongsHebrew)

: 24 'abiyb aw-beeb' from an unused root (meaning to be tender); green, i.e. a young ear of grain; hence, the name of the month Abib or Nisan:--Abib, ear, green ears of corn (not maize). (StrongsHebrew)

: 25 'Abiy Gib`own ab-ee' ghib-one' from 1 and 1391; father (i.e. founder) of Gibon; Abi-Gibon, perhaps an Israelite:--father of Gibeon. see HEBREW for 01 see HEBREW for 01391 (StrongsHebrew)

: 26 'Abiygayil ab-ee-gah'-yil or shorter Abiygal {ab-ee-gal'}; from 1 and 1524; father (i.e. source) of joy; Abigail or Abigal, the name of two Israelitesses:--Abigal. see HEBREW for 01 see HEBREW for 01524 (StrongsHebrew)

: 27 'Abiydan ab-ee-dawn' from 1 and 1777; father of judgment (i.e. judge); Abidan, an Israelite:--Abidan. see HEBREW for 01 see HEBREW for 01777 (StrongsHebrew)

: 28 'Abiyda` ab-ee-daw' from 1 and 3045; father of knowledge (i.e. knowing); Abida, a son of Abraham by Keturah:--Abida, Abidah. see HEBREW for 01 see HEBREW for 03045 (StrongsHebrew)

: 29 'Abiyah ab-ee-yaw' or prolonged Abiyahuw {ab-ee-yaw'-hoo}; from 1 and 3050; father (i.e. worshipper) of Jah; Abijah, the name of several Israelite men and two Israelitesses:--Abiah, Abijah. see HEBREW for 01 see HEBREW for 03050 (StrongsHebrew)

: 30 'Abiyhuw' ab-ee-hoo' from 1 and 1931; father (i.e. worshipper) of Him (i.e. God); Abihu, a son of Aaron:--Abihu. see HEBREW for 01 see HEBREW for 01931 (StrongsHebrew)

: 31 'Abiyhuwd ab-ee-hood' from 1 and 1935; father (i.e. possessor) of renown; Abihud, the name of two Israelites:--Abihud. see HEBREW for 01 see HEBREW for 01935 (StrongsHebrew)

: 32 'Abiyhayil ab-ee-hah'-yil or (more correctly) hAbiychayil {ab-ee- khah'-yil}; from 1 and 2428; father (i.e. possessor) of might; Abihail or Abichail, the name of three Israelites and two Israelitesses:--Abihail. see HEBREW for 02428 (StrongsHebrew)

: 33 'Abiy ha-`Ezriy ab-ee'-haw-ez-ree' from 44 with the article inserted; father of the Ezrite; an Abiezrite or descendant of Abiezer; -- Abiezrite. see HEBREW for 044 (StrongsHebrew)

: 34 'ebyown eb-yone' from 14, in the sense of want (especially in feeling); destitute:--beggar, needy, poor (man). see HEBREW for 014 (StrongsHebrew)

: 35 'abiyownah ab-ee-yo-naw' from 14; provocative of desire; the caper berry (from its stimulative taste):--desire. see HEBREW for 014 (StrongsHebrew)

: 36 'Abiytuwb ab-ee-toob' from 1 and 2898; father of goodness (i.e. good); Abitub, an Israelite:--Abitub. see HEBREW for 01 see HEBREW for 02898 (StrongsHebrew)

: 37 'Abiytal ab-ee-tal' from 1 and 2919; father of dew (i.e. fresh); Abital, a wife of King David:--Abital. see HEBREW for 01 see HEBREW for 02919 (StrongsHebrew)

: 38 'Abiyam ab-ee-yawm' from 1 and 3220; father of (the) sea (i.e. seaman); Abijam (or Abijah), a king of Judah:--Abijam. see HEBREW for 01 see HEBREW for 03220 (StrongsHebrew)

: 39 'Abiyma'el ab-ee-maw-ale' from 1 and an elsewhere unused (probably foreign) word; father of Mael (apparently some Arab tribe); Abimael, a son of Joktan:--Abimael. see HEBREW for 01 (StrongsHebrew)

: 40 'Abiymelek ab-ee-mel'-ek from 1 and 4428; father of (the) king; Abimelek, the name of two Philistine kings and of two Israelites:--Abimelech. see HEBREW for 01 see HEBREW for 04428 (StrongsHebrew)

: 43 'Ebyacaph eb-yaw-sawf' contracted from 23; Ebjasaph, an Israelite:--Ebiasaph. see HEBREW for 023 (StrongsHebrew)

: 44 'Abiy`ezer ab-ee-ay'-zer from 1 and 5829; father of help (i.e. helpful); Abiezer, the name of two Israelites:--Abiezer. see HEBREW for 01 see HEBREW for 05829 (StrongsHebrew)

: 45 'Abiy-`albown ab-ee-al-bone' from 1 and and an unused root of uncertain. derivation; probably, father of strength (i.e. valiant); Abialbon, an Israelite:--Abialbon. see HEBREW for 01 (StrongsHebrew)

: 46 'abiyr aw-beer' from 82; mighty (spoken of God):--mighty (one). see HEBREW for 082 (StrongsHebrew)

: 47 'abbiyr ab-beer' for 46; --angel, bull, chiefest, mighty (one), stout(-hearted), strong (one), valiant. see HEBREW for 046 (StrongsHebrew)

: 49 'Abiyshag ab-ee-shag' from 1 and 7686; father of error (i.e. blundering); Abishag, a concubine of David:--Abishag. see HEBREW for 01 see HEBREW for 07686 (StrongsHebrew)

: 52 'Abiyshay ab-ee-shah'ee or (shorter) Abshay {ab-shah'ee}; from 1 and 7862; father of a gift (i.e. probably generous); Abishai, an Israelite:--Abishai. see HEBREW for 01 see HEBREW for 07862 (StrongsHebrew)

: 53 'Abiyshalowm ab-ee-shaw-lome' or (shortened) bAbshalowm {ab-shaw- lome'}; from 1 and 7965; father of peace (i.e. friendly); Abshalom, a son of David; also (the fuller form) a later Israelite:--Abishalom, Absalom. see HEBREW for 01 see HEBREW for 07965 (StrongsHebrew)

: 68 'eben eh'-ben from the root of 1129 through the meaning to build; a stone:--+ carbuncle, + mason, + plummet, (chalk-, hail-, head-, sling-)stone(-ny), (divers) weight(-s). see HEBREW for 01129 (StrongsHebrew)

: 8659 Tarshiysh tar-sheesh' probably the same as 8658 (as the region of the stone, or the reverse); Tarshish, a place on the Mediterranean, hence, the ephithet of a merchant vessel (as if for or from that port); also the name of a Persian and of an Israelite:--Tarshish, Tharshish. see HEBREW for 08658 (StrongsHebrew)
